Detailed Description

cvmx_ase_lue_dbg_ctl0

We are not rewiring the NSP's 16-bit debug bus. Instead we are duplicating that mux 4 times to give CNXXXX better observability. LUE DBGCTX is a DOR daisy-chained through the TWE and BWE engines, it can't be moved to a straight CNXXXX debug bus without rewriting the whole thing. This register selects engines for debug observations for the LUE's four 16-bit debug muxes and selects context for observation.
